{
  "texts": [
    "In this work we use three channels with forgetting constants k 1 = 0.8, k 2 = 0.6 and k 3 = 0.4, so the input of the DNN estimator is a tensor of shape [3, H, W].",
    "1 Figure 7.17Figure 7.",
    "For training, original sequences of time surfaces are divided in subsequences which are then fed to the DNN in a random order.",
    "For validation/test data, the original sequence is not subdivided to emulate the behavior of the final system.",
    "Figure 8.8Figure 8."
  ]
